  "app_custom_tools": [
    {
      "tool_id": "ctool-import-txns",
      "name": "Import Bank Transactions",
      "description": "Imports and categorizes bank and credit card transactions for month-end processing.",
      "description_md": "Combines checking and credit card CSVs, deduplicates, and counts transactions for downstream processing.",
      "category": "bookkeeping",
      "code": "const checking = api.getParameter('checking_data') || '';\nconst creditCard = api.getParameter('credit_card_data') || '';\n\nconst checkingLines = checking.split('\\n').slice(1).filter(l => l.trim());\nconst ccLines = creditCard.split('\\n').slice(1).filter(l => l.trim());\n\nconst summary = {\n  checking_count: checkingLines.length,\n  credit_card_count: ccLines.length,\n  total: checkingLines.length + ccLines.length\n};\n\napi.setParameter('categorized_data', JSON.stringify(summary));\napi.setParameter('all_transactions', checking + '\\n' + creditCard);\nreturn { status: 'success', statusMessage: 'Imported ' + summary.total + ' transactions' };",
      "definition_json": "{\"parameters\":[{\"name\":\"checking_data\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Checking account CSV\",\"required\":false},{\"name\":\"credit_card_data\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Credit card CSV\",\"required\":false}],\"outputs\":[{\"name\":\"categorized_data\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"JSON transaction summary\"},{\"name\":\"all_transactions\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Combined raw transactions\"}]}",
      "chat_history": null,
      "created_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z"
    },
    {
      "tool_id": "ctool-ar-aging",
      "name": "AR Aging Calculator",
      "description": "Calculates accounts receivable aging buckets from invoice data.",
      "description_md": "Reads invoice CSV data and sorts outstanding invoices into aging buckets: Current, 1-30 days, 31-60 days, 61-90 days, and 90+ days overdue.",
      "category": "bookkeeping",
      "code": "const invoices = api.getParameter('invoices_data') || '';\nconst lines = invoices.split('\\n').slice(1).filter(l => l.trim());\nconst today = new Date();\n\nconst buckets = { current: 0, days_30: 0, days_60: 0, days_90: 0, over_90: 0 };\nconst overdue = [];\n\nfor (const line of lines) {\n  const parts = line.split(',');\n  if (parts.length < 5) continue;\n  const [invoice_id, client, amount, issue_date, due_date, status] = parts;\n  if (status && status.trim().toLowerCase() === 'paid') continue;\n\n  const due = new Date(due_date);\n  const daysOverdue = Math.floor((today - due) / (1000 * 60 * 60 * 24));\n  const amt = parseFloat(amount) || 0;\n\n  if (daysOverdue <= 0) buckets.current += amt;\n  else if (daysOverdue <= 30) { buckets.days_30 += amt; overdue.push({ invoice_id, client, amount: amt, days: daysOverdue }); }\n  else if (daysOverdue <= 60) { buckets.days_60 += amt; overdue.push({ invoice_id, client, amount: amt, days: daysOverdue }); }\n  else if (daysOverdue <= 90) { buckets.days_90 += amt; overdue.push({ invoice_id, client, amount: amt, days: daysOverdue }); }\n  else { buckets.over_90 += amt; overdue.push({ invoice_id, client, amount: amt, days: daysOverdue }); }\n}\n\napi.setParameter('aging_data', JSON.stringify({ buckets, overdue, total_outstanding: Object.values(buckets).reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) }));\nreturn { status: 'success', statusMessage: overdue.length + ' overdue invoices found' };",
      "definition_json": "{\"parameters\":[{\"name\":\"invoices_data\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"Invoice CSV: invoice_id, client, amount, issue_date, due_date, status\",\"required\":true}],\"outputs\":[{\"name\":\"aging_data\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"JSON aging analysis with buckets and overdue list\"}]}",
      "chat_history": null,
      "created_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z"
    },
    {
      "tool_id": "ctool-ar-html",
      "name": "AR Aging Report",
      "description": "Generates an HTML accounts receivable aging report.",
      "description_md": "Takes AR aging data and produces a styled HTML report with aging buckets, overdue invoice details, and collection priority flags.",
      "category": "bookkeeping",
      "code": "const agingJson = api.getParameter('aging_data') || '{}';\nlet data;\ntry { data = JSON.parse(agingJson); } catch (e) { data = { buckets: {}, overdue: [], total_outstanding: 0 }; }\n\nconst b = data.buckets || {};\nconst overdueRows = (data.overdue || []).map(function(inv) {\n  return '<tr><td>' + inv.invoice_id + '</td><td>' + inv.client + '</td><td>$' + inv.amount.toFixed(2) + '</td><td class=\"' + (inv.days > 60 ? 'critical' : inv.days > 30 ? 'warn' : 'late') + '\">' + inv.days + ' days</td></tr>';\n}).join('');\n\nconst html = '<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html><head><title>AR Aging Report</title>\\n<style>body{font-family:system-ui;max-width:800px;margin:2rem auto;padding:0 1rem}table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse}th,td{padding:8px 12px;border:1px solid #ddd;text-align:left}th{background:#f5f5f5}.late{color:#d97706}.warn{color:#ea580c}.critical{color:#dc2626;font-weight:600}.bucket{display:inline-block;padding:0.5rem 1rem;margin:0.25rem;border-radius:6px;text-align:center}.bucket .amount{font-size:1.25rem;font-weight:700}.bucket .label{font-size:0.75rem;color:#6b7280}</style></head>\\n<body><h1>Accounts Receivable Aging</h1>\\n<p>Generated: ' + new Date().toLocaleDateString() + '</p>\\n<div>\\n<span class=\"bucket\" style=\"background:#ecfdf5\"><div class=\"amount\">$' + (b.current||0).toFixed(2) + '</div><div class=\"label\">Current</div></span>\\n<span class=\"bucket\" style=\"background:#fef9c3\"><div class=\"amount\">$' + (b.days_30||0).toFixed(2) + '</div><div class=\"label\">1-30 Days</div></span>\\n<span class=\"bucket\" style=\"background:#fed7aa\"><div class=\"amount\">$' + (b.days_60||0).toFixed(2) + '</div><div class=\"label\">31-60 Days</div></span>\\n<span class=\"bucket\" style=\"background:#fecaca\"><div class=\"amount\">$' + (b.days_90||0).toFixed(2) + '</div><div class=\"label\">61-90 Days</div></span>\\n<span class=\"bucket\" style=\"background:#fca5a5\"><div class=\"amount\">$' + (b.over_90||0).toFixed(2) + '</div><div class=\"label\">90+ Days</div></span>\\n</div>\\n<h2>Overdue Invoices</h2>\\n' + (overdueRows ? '<table><thead><tr><th>Invoice</th><th>Client</th><th>Amount</th><th>Days Overdue</th></tr></thead><tbody>' + overdueRows + '</tbody></table>' : '<p>No overdue invoices.</p>') + '\\n<p style=\"margin-top:2rem;font-weight:600\">Total Outstanding: $' + (data.total_outstanding||0).toFixed(2) + '</p>\\n</body></html>';\n\napi.setParameter('html_report', html);\nreturn { status: 'success', statusMessage: 'AR report generated' };",
      "definition_json": "{\"parameters\":[{\"name\":\"aging_data\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"JSON aging data from AR Aging Calculator\",\"required\":true}],\"outputs\":[{\"name\":\"html_report\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"HTML AR aging report\"}]}",
      "chat_history": null,
      "created_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z"
    },
    {
      "tool_id": "ctool-expense-html",
      "name": "Expense Report Generator",
      "description": "Generates an HTML expense report from AI-categorized transactions.",
      "description_md": "Takes categorized transaction JSON and produces a styled expense report grouped by GL account with totals.",
      "category": "bookkeeping",
      "code": "const categorizedJson = api.getParameter('categorized_json') || '[]';\nlet transactions;\ntry { transactions = JSON.parse(categorizedJson); } catch (e) { transactions = []; }\n\nconst byAccount = {};\nfor (const txn of transactions) {\n  const acct = txn.account || 'Uncategorized';\n  if (!byAccount[acct]) byAccount[acct] = { total: 0, count: 0 };\n  byAccount[acct].total += Math.abs(txn.amount || 0);\n  byAccount[acct].count++;\n}\n\nconst rows = Object.entries(byAccount)\n  .sort(function(a, b) { return b[1].total - a[1].total; })\n  .map(function(pair) { return '<tr><td>' + pair[0] + '</td><td>' + pair[1].count + '</td><td>$' + pair[1].total.toFixed(2) + '</td></tr>'; })\n  .join('');\n\nconst grandTotal = Object.values(byAccount).reduce(function(sum, d) { return sum + d.total; }, 0);\n\nconst html = '<!DOCTYPE html>\\n<html><head><title>Expense Report</title>\\n<style>body{font-family:system-ui;max-width:800px;margin:2rem auto;padding:0 1rem}table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse}th,td{padding:8px 12px;border:1px solid #ddd;text-align:left}th{background:#f5f5f5}.total{font-weight:700;background:#fafafa}</style></head>\\n<body><h1>Expense Report by Account</h1>\\n<p>Generated: ' + new Date().toLocaleDateString() + '</p>\\n<table><thead><tr><th>GL Account</th><th>Transactions</th><th>Total</th></tr></thead>\\n<tbody>' + rows + '\\n<tr class=\"total\"><td>Grand Total</td><td>' + transactions.length + '</td><td>$' + grandTotal.toFixed(2) + '</td></tr>\\n</tbody></table></body></html>';\n\napi.setParameter('html_report', html);\nreturn { status: 'success', statusMessage: 'Expense report generated' };",
      "definition_json": "{\"parameters\":[{\"name\":\"categorized_json\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"JSON array of categorized transactions from LLM step\",\"required\":true}],\"outputs\":[{\"name\":\"html_report\",\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"HTML expense report\"}]}",
      "chat_history": null,
      "created_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
  "app_sessions": [],
  "app_knowledge": [
    {
      "skill_id": "skill-bookkeeping",
      "name": "Small Business Bookkeeping",
      "content": "# Small Business Bookkeeping\n\nThis workspace manages bookkeeping for a small service/consulting business.\n\n## Getting Started\nThis workspace comes pre-loaded with a chart of accounts and 3 months of sample transactions (Jan–Mar 2025). You can run **View Financial Reports** immediately to see P&L, Balance Sheet, and Cash Flow.\n\n## Workflows\n\n### View Financial Reports (no AI key needed)\nRuns instantly. Generates P&L, Balance Sheet, and Cash Flow from the pre-loaded GL data.\n\n### Invoice & AR Tracker (no AI key needed)\nCalculates aging buckets from invoice data and generates an HTML report. Load your invoice CSV as `invoices` user data.\n\n### Expense Categorization (requires AI key)\nUses AI to categorize bank transactions to GL accounts. Load your bank CSV as `checking` and/or `credit_card` user data.\n\n## Data Sources\n- **checking**: Business checking account transactions (CSV: date, description, amount)\n- **credit_card**: Business credit card transactions (CSV: date, description, amount)\n- **invoices**: Outstanding invoices (CSV: invoice_id, client, amount, issue_date, due_date, status)\n\n## Chart of Accounts\n\n### Assets (1xxx)\n- 1000 Checking, 1010 Savings, 1100 Accounts Receivable, 1200 Equipment\n\n### Liabilities (2xxx)\n- 2000 Credit Card, 2100 Accounts Payable\n\n### Equity (3xxx)\n- 3000 Owner Equity, 3050 Owner Draw, 3100 Retained Earnings\n\n### Revenue (4xxx)\n- 4000 Service Revenue, 4100 Product Revenue\n\n### Expenses (5xxx)\n- 5000 Rent, 5010 Utilities, 5020 Office Supplies, 5030 Software & Subscriptions\n- 5040 Insurance, 5050 Professional Services, 5060 Marketing, 5070 Travel\n- 5080 Meals & Entertainment, 5090 Payroll, 5900 Miscellaneous\n\n## Monthly Close Process\n1. Download bank statements as CSV and load them as `checking` and `credit_card`\n2. Run **Expense Categorization** to tag transactions to GL accounts\n3. Review categorizations (check low-confidence items)\n4. Post reviewed entries via chat: ask the AI to post specific entries to the GL\n5. Run **View Financial Reports** to see updated statements\n6. Download reports for your records\n\n## Tips\n- Run **View Financial Reports** first to see the pre-loaded sample data\n- Categorize transactions soon after downloading — descriptions are freshest\n- Review AI categorizations for accuracy, especially new vendors\n- Run AR aging weekly to stay on top of collections\n- Keep invoice CSV updated when payments come in (change status to 'paid')",
      "summary": "Guide for small business bookkeeping: workflows overview, chart of accounts, monthly close process, and tips.",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-03T00:00:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
